.TH PAGER 1
.SH NAME
pager \- display postscript, pdf, and other pages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pager
[
.B -p
.I port
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Pager
creates and reads a
.IR portfs (4)
.B postscript
port (or
.I port
when given). Messages sent to the port are correspond to a
files to be shown using
.IR page (1)
in the screen where the program was started.
.PP
This is useful to ask the system to show documents at a particular
system, by starting this program on that system.
.SH SOURCE
.B /sys/src/cmd/pager.c
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR page (1).


